Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Volcan Fall; Credicorp Gains

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-12-01T17:47:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-01/peru-stocks-buenaventura-volcan-fall-credicorp-gains.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 12:21 p.m. Lima time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell 1.1 percent to 19,684.77. The
 MSCI All Peru Capped Index  eased 0.8 percent to 2,550.11.  Mining companies declined as copper and zinc prices dropped
on concern that demand will slow after manufacturing shrank in
 China , the world’s top consumer of industrial metals.  Volcan Cia. Minera SAA  (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc
producer, retreated 4.6 percent to 3.09 soles.  Alturas Minerals
Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian copper exploration company, dropped
10 percent to 9 cents.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the world’s
fourth-largest tin producer, fell 1.9 percent to 2.65 soles.  Gold companies fell as the precious metal declined in  New
York .  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN)  , the country’s
biggest precious-metals miner, fell 3 percent to $38.20, a six-
week low.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold
exploration company, eased 3.7 percent to $3.37.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial-services
company, rose 1.2 percent to $109.30, a one-month high. The
company’s Banco de Credito del Peru unit agreed to buy a 51
percent stake in  Colombia ’s Correval to expand its brokerage and
corporate finance business.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
 jquigley8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
